    contribute back. Distribute the Software or your modified version under
    this license. Distribute the Software's binaries together with a
    platform it runs on (e.g., an OS or runtime image). Build plugins that
    run with DevCntr (without bundling DevCntr with your plugin).

  * YOU MAY NOT: Pretend your fork or product is the official DevCntr or
    run a competing "DevCntr" company without permission. Bundle this
    Software into your own product or ship it inside your app's installer as
    a value-added tool. Use the DevCntr name or branding without
    permission. Do abusive or malicious things with the Software (see full
    terms below).

The full license below is what governs your rights and obligations.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This license makes the DevCntr software source-available: you may view,
use, and modify the Software under the terms below. Commercial use is
permitted (e.g., you may make and sell your own software), but you may not
incorporate the Software into your own product (see below). You may
distribute binaries of the Software together with a platform the Software
runs on (e.g., an OS image or runtime distribution). You may not bundle the
Software as a value-added side-tool for your product—for example, you may
not ship the Software inside another application's installer on the same
platform the Software runs on. Plugins, extensions, or add-ons that work with
DevCntr may use the Software in the ordinary way (your plugin runs with
DevCntr; you do not bundle DevCntr with your plugin). You may not
offer a competing product or business that substitutes for the official Dev
Center project without separate written permission. Branding and certain
distributions remain restricted.

================================================================================
1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

"Software" means source code, documentation, configuration, and other
materials in this repository, except Branding.

"Branding" means the names "DevCntr", "devcntr-org", "The DevCntr",
and any variant that suggests official or endorsed origin; all logos, icons,
splash screens, and visual identity; and any trade dress that would cause
confusion with the official DevCntr product. Branding is NOT licensed under
this document. Use of Branding requires separate written permission from the
copyright holder.

"Competing Use" means using the Software or any derivative (including forks)
to operate, offer, market, or promote a product, service, or business that
competes with or substitutes for the official DevCntr project—for example,
offering your own "DevCntr" company, a near-identical fork as a product or
service, or a paid alternative that replaces DevCntr. Competing Use
requires prior written permission from the copyright holder and is not
granted under this license.

"Incorporation" means distributing, bundling, embedding, or otherwise
including the Software (or a derivative) as part of your own product or
software, so that your product ships with or is built on the Software as a
component—for example, shipping the Software inside another application's
installer on the same platform the Software runs on, as a value-added or
bundled side-tool. You may not incorporate the Software into your product.
Incorporation does not include: (a) distributing binaries of the Software
together with a platform the Software runs on (e.g., an operating system,
runtime, or distribution image); or (b) developing or distributing a plugin,
extension, or add-on that is designed to work with DevCntr and that is
used in the ordinary way (the user runs DevCntr separately; your plugin
runs with or within DevCntr; you do not distribute the Software as part
of your plugin). Incorporation is not granted under this license.

"Prohibited Distribution" means any distribution of the Software (or a
derivative) that:

  (a) is a frivolous or duplicate listing in an app store, marketplace, or
      similar distribution channel that adds no substantial value (e.g., a
      near-identical copy with no meaningful improvement or differentiation);

  (b) is malicious (e.g., contains malware, steals data, or harms users); or

  (c) is cognitively or commercially abusive, including but not limited to:
      stuffing the product with ads, dark patterns, or monetization that
      exploits users or the reputation of this project without adding
      commensurate value.

