================================================================================
3. RESERVED RIGHTS: NO INCORPORATION; NO COMPETING USE; BRANDING
================================================================================

3.1 No Incorporation. No right is granted to incorporate the Software (or any
derivative) into your own product or software. You may not bundle the
Software as a value-added side-tool for your product—for example, you may
not ship the Software inside another application's installer on the same
platform the Software runs on. You may not otherwise embed, ship, or attach
the Software to your product so that your product includes or is built on the
Software as a component. This prohibition does not apply to: (a) distributing
binaries of the Software together with a platform the Software runs on (e.g.,
an OS image, runtime, or distribution); or (b) plugins, extensions, or
add-ons that work with DevCntr in the ordinary way (the user runs Dev
Center separately; your plugin runs with or within DevCntr; you do not
distribute the Software as part of your plugin). Incorporation requires
prior written permission from the copyright holder.

3.2 No Competing Use. No right is granted to use the Software or any
derivative (including forks) to run, offer, or promote a company, product, or
service that competes with or substitutes for the official DevCntr
project (e.g., your own "DevCntr" or a near-identical alternative).
Competing Use requires prior written permission from the copyright holder.

3.3 Branding. No right is granted to use Branding. You may not use the names,
logos, or trade dress of DevCntr to imply endorsement, official status, or
origin from the copyright holder unless you have separate written permission.
Forked or derivative products must not present themselves as "DevCntr" or
as official or endorsed versions without such permission.

================================================================================
4. PROHIBITED CONDUCT AND PENALTIES
================================================================================

4.1 Prohibition. You may not (a) create, publish, or maintain any Prohibited
Distribution, (b) engage in Incorporation, or (c) engage in Competing Use.
Doing any of the foregoing constitutes a material breach of this license and
violation of the copyright holder's rights.

4.2 Consequences of breach.

  (a) All rights granted under this license terminate automatically, worldwide,
      as to you and any entity you control or that engages in the breach (e.g.,
      Prohibited Distribution, Incorporation, or Competing Use) with your
      knowledge or participation.

  (b) You agree that actual damages for a Prohibited Distribution,
      Incorporation, or Competing Use are difficult to ascertain and that the
      following amounts are reasonable estimates of harm and not penalties:
      (i) liquidated damages of fifty thousand United States dollars (USD
      50,000) per distinct Prohibited Distribution, per distinct instance of
      Incorporation, or per distinct instance of Competing Use (e.g., per app
      store listing, per product that incorporates the Software, or per
      competing offering or business), and (ii) an additional
      fifty thousand United States dollars (USD 50,000) if the Prohibited
      Distribution is malicious or cognitively abusive as described in
      Section 1(c). The copyright holder may seek these amounts in addition to
      any other remedies.

  (c) The copyright holder is entitled to seek injunctive relief (including
      removal of listings, cessation of distribution, cessation of
      Incorporation, and cessation of Competing Use) without proof of monetary
      harm.

  (d) In any action to enforce this license or redress a Prohibited
      Distribution, Incorporation, or Competing Use, the prevailing party may
      recover reasonable attorneys' fees and costs from the non-prevailing party.

4.3 The remedies in this Section 4 are cumulative and not exclusive of any
other remedies at law or in equity.

